				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Pesky Drood<a name="40795"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 19 04 3:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At level 30, you have fewer tools to work with. But the root can be removed with your level 22 cancel magic song. Just set up your buffs so that his root, snare or dot will be the top buffs and then cancel them off. With no good way to mana drain him, if I were you I would buy a pumice stone in POK. U can click it from inventory with him targetted and it will strip 4 buffs from him. 
<br />

<br />
My guess is your best bet is to strip his buffs with a pumice stone (his DS is a worry for you so make sure it is stripped), and then snare and melee him down. Before I did that though I would test how well I could attack him with amp + bellows and fufills. You could try charming a pet onto him, but realistically with the short duration of charm at your level you are more likely buying trouble for yourself than presenting a problem for him.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
65 Bard of Torv</span></td>
